The paper discusses the use of term suggestion modules in digital libraries, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on the social sciences digital library Sowiport, which involves the use of machine learning and data mining techniques (cs.DL) to improve search results. The paper also mentions the use of thesaurus terms and author names, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
